Block.Name: Multi-Robot Environment

Mask.Description:
Displays map, waypoint, and object data for a multi-robot simulation.
Use "Multi-Robot Visualizer" blocks to display individual robots in this environment.

MaskParameter.Name: showObjects

Mask.Description:
Supply the pose and (optionally) lidar ranges for a single robot in a multi-robot setup.
These blocks require a "Multi-Robot Environment" block to exist in the model.

MaskParameter.Name: hasLidar
hasObjDetector

Mask.Description:
Kinematics-only (motion actuated) Simscape Multibody Model of a differential drive vehicle.
Inputs: Left and right wheel speeds [wL; wR], in rad/s Pose [x; y; theta], in m, m, and rad/s, respectively
Connection Ports: R: Reference frame at center of vehicle G: Ground/world location

Calculates the forward kinematics for a differential drive vehicle.
Input: [wL; wR], the left and right wheel speeds (rad/s)
Output: [v; w], the linear (m/s) and angular (rad/s) velocities of the vehicle

Calculates the forward kinematics for a differential drive vehicle.
Input: [v; w], the linear (m/s) and angular (rad/s) velocities of the vehicle
Output: [wL; wR], the left and right wheel speeds (rad/s)

Simulates the kinematics of a differential drive vehicle from a specified initial pose.
Input: Left and right wheel speeds [wL; wR], in rad/s
Output: Pose [x; y; theta], in m, m, and rad
Set the Sample Time parameter to 0 for continuous-time simulation, or a positive number for discrete-time simulation.

Mask.Description:
Kinematics-only (motion actuated) Simscape Multibody Model of a four-wheeled vehicle with front and rear drive and steering.
Input: Wheel speeds [wf; wr] (rad/s) Steer angles [phif; phir] (rad) Pose [x; y; theta], in m, m, and rad/s, respectively
Connection Ports: R: Reference frame at center of vehicle G: Ground/world location

Calculates the forward kinematics for a four-wheeled vehicle with front and rear drive and steering.
Input: Wheel speeds [wf; wr] (rad/s) Steer angles [phif; phir] (rad)
Output: Vehicle velocities [vx; vy; w] in body coordinates (m/s, m/s, and rad/s)

Calculates the inverse kinematics for a four-wheeled vehicle with front and rear drive and steering.
Input: Vehicle velocities [vx; vy; w] in body coordinates (m/s, m/s, and rad/s) In Front Steering and Zero Sideslip mode, the velocity inputs used are forward and angular speed [vx;w] In Parallel Steering mode, the velocity inputs used are forward and lateral speed [vx;vy]
Output: Wheel speeds [wf; wr] (rad/s) Steer angles [phif; phir] (rad)

Simulates the kinematics of a four-wheeled vehicle with front and rear drive and steering, from a specified initial pose.
Input: Wheel speeds [wf; wr] (rad/s) Steer angles [phif; phir] (rad)
Output: Pose [x; y; theta], in m, m, and rad
Set the Sample Time parameter to 0 for continuous-time simulation, or a positive number for discrete-time simulation.

Mask.Description:
Converts a 2D velocity input [vx;vy;w] from body (vehicle) coordinates to world (global) coordinates.
vx = Linear velocity in x-direction (longitudinal) vy = Linear velocity in y-direction (lateral) w = Angular velocity (about z-axis)

Simulates the kinematics of a generic vehicle, from a specified initial pose.
Input: Body velocities [vx; vy; w], in m/s, m/s, and rad/s
Output: Pose [x; y; theta], in m, m, and rad
Set the Sample Time parameter to 0 for continuous-time simulation, or a positive number for discrete-time simulation.

vx = Linear velocity in x-direction (longitudinal) vy = Linear velocity in y-direction (lateral) w = Angular velocity (about z-axis)
